d valign=top background=http://home.earthlink.net/~nsmessageboard/ezboard/images/bar.jpg class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=spaceguy3>SpaceGuy3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/22/03 11:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=348.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/poll_icon.gif" align=absmiddle>  Lets build a small, reusable spaceplane</span><hr size=1> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Should we first build a small, reusable, nuclear core spaceplane?  I propose a 4 person capable space plane with small payload capacity or 7 person capacity with no payload.  Keep the design simple, horizontal take-off and landing, small nuclear ceramic core, LEO capable, Kerosene or jet fuel for fuel (ease and length of storage), with all fuel stored internally.   Using Kerosene or jet fuel would mean the plane could be serviced for takeoff at any major airport hub.  <br>
<br>
The plane itself could be developed and built in a few years time, and the nuclear core added after it is developed, for a fully usable, fully capable spaceplane.  Reentry would be a traditional reentry profile with a glided landing at any major airport, so additional fuel would not be needed for a slow, powered reentry.</FONT><FORM method=post action="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.processVote?topicID=348.topic"><table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width="55%"><tbody><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="1"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Yes, lets start small and use this as the model for bigger and better things to come!</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="2"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Lets build it, but lets also build the bigger launchers now also</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="3"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I agree with a spaceplane concept, but lets build a commercial airliner size space plane</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="4"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>No, lets stick to nuclear powered traditional rocket type launchers</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="5"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Lets not develop nuclear anything</FONT></td></tr></tbody></table><P><input type=submit value="Vote"></form><a HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showMessage?topicID=348.topic&pollResults=on><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Show results</FONT></A> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yales>yales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1311<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/22/03 12:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=348.topic&index=1>Reply<