<br>
A 4 man spaceplane is well within chemical SSTO capability and this is the best way to go for what is probabaly going to be a crew transfer/small satalite vehicle.<br>
<br>
Atomic engines are more suited for larger, less frequent, missions such as launching very large satalites or space ship/station componants where their enourmous power capabilities come into their own.<br>
<br>
See <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/space/nuclearmauk2/" target="top">www.angelfire.com/space/nuclearmauk2/</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
