The only risk is to the passengers. They are at the opposite end of the ship, separated by distance and fuel tanks, and with sheilding limited to the living areas.<br>
<br>
WITHIN the biosphere however, space-bound reactors are a fearsome risk and either outlawed (as in Orion) or discouraged by national and international agreements.<br>
<br>
Reactor rocket launchers ARE -technically- feasable (altho not the specific design from the link a couple of posts up), they simply a future technology who's time is past.<br>
<br>
In the same time period it would take to design, test, and create a nuclear booster (and then not be able to use it) a space elevator may be possible. In any event, combustion based  systems can and will do the job.<br>
<br>
